Definition of Done:

Done for a feature:
Unit tests pass
Able to run server after code is saved
Basic definition of feature can be used by anyone
No other feature is broken because of this new feature
Peer reviewed code in meeting (check for clean code)

Done for a Sprint:
All user stories were finished (Scrum board has all tasks in done)
Features usable, no features conflict or cause different parts to break
Product could be “potentially” given to customer

Done for Release:
All System and unit tests pass (see our “System and Unit Test Report” in Release 1.0 docs)
Acceptance Test passed
